name: the-streamcat-dataset-accumulated-attributes-for-nhdplusv2-version-2-1-catchments-for-the-conte
notes: This dataset represents geochemical or geophysical attributes in surface or near surface geology within individual, local NHDPlusV2 catchments and upstream, contributing watersheds. Attributes of the landscape layer were calculated for every local NHDPlusV2 catchment and accumulated to provide watershed-level metrics. (See Supplementary Info for Glossary of Terms) For information regarding how the Landscape layers were created see https://www.sciencebase.gov/catalog/item/53481333e4b06f6ce034aae7. Landscape Layers are partitioned into 4 tables based on the location of no-data cells within their rasters to correctly reflect the PctFull attributes within each table (see Data Structure and Attribute Information for a description).
